The paper deals with problems related to convex polygons and their properties in Cartesian products (grids) of sets of real numbers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents algorithms for computing the largest convex chain and approximating the maximum size of a supported convex polygon, which are problems related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses exponential bounds on the maximum number of convex polygons, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
